1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,500
Welcome to ZK Dungeon, a decentralized rogue-lite experience built for the DoraHacks Stellar ZK Gaming track.

2
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:15,000
This demo showcases our single-player MVP in Hackathon Mode, running entirely on the Stellar Testnet.

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:25,000
We begin by connecting our Freighter wallet in testnet mode. In this solo instance, the player goes up against the house.

4
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:35,000
Connecting the wallet initiates our game session and prepares the on-chain state to track our progress.

5
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Instead of relying on a centralized server to validate moves, ZK Dungeon targets verifiable zero-knowledge gaming.

6
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:56,000
When a player makes a choice, a zero-knowledge proof is generated locally on the client.

7
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:05,000
This ensures the player's moves are valid without revealing the dungeon's underlying cryptographic secrets.

8
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Once generated, this proof is submitted to the Stellar Testnet via the connected Freighter wallet.

9
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:25,000
A Stellar smart contract then verifies the proof on-chain, acting as an impartial, decentralized referee.

10
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:37,000
This combination of off-chain ZK execution and on-chain verification guarantees a provably fair game.

11
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:45,000
When the run concludes, the game settles the outcome cryptographically.

12
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:54,000
True 2-player state channels are actively in progress, but the core ZK verification loop is firmly in place today.

13
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Thank you for watching, and good luck to all teams in the Stellar ZK Gaming hackathon.
